\cf2 \cb6 At a\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.att.com/Common/about_us/files/pdf/analyst_presentation_bw.pdf"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 \strokec5 much-reported analyst conference yesterday}},\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.forbes.com/companies/att/"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 \strokec5 AT&T}}\'a0announced plans to accelerate upgrades to both its wired and mobile networks, pledging an additional $14 billion over the next three years, in addition to several billion already committed.\
When completed in 2015, according to the company, the new infrastructure will offer AT&T customers faster and more reliable network facilities, which will operate natively in Internet Protocol (IP).\'a0 Text, voice, and data will begin life as packets, travel through the network as packets, and arrive on customer devices as packets.\
